org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulators

Interface ListData<E,T extends ListData<E,T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of element involved in the collection
    E - The implementing item data that should be comparable to itself
    All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<T>, DataManipulator<T>, DataSerializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AchievementData, AttributeData, BanData, BreakableData, ConnectedDirectionData, FireworkData, LoreData, PagedData, PlaceableData, PotionEffectData, TargetLivingData, TradeOfferData

    public interface ListData<E,T extends ListData<E,T>>
extends DataManipulator<T>
    Represents an item that can have a Collection of types of elements. Since DataManipulator is meant to be mutable, the ListData too is mutable.

    The various implementations of ListData include: PagedData, LoreData, and PlaceableData.

      • getAll

        List<E> getAll()
        Gets all the elements stored by this ListData.

        This will return an unmodifiable list of elements. To modify the list of elements, use the provided methods in ListData. The returned list will have non-null values.

        Returns:
        An unmodifiable list of all elements

      • add

        void add(int index,
         E element)
        Adds the given element at the end of this ListData.

        If there are elements at the given index, the given element is inserted and pushes the rest of the elements back. If there are no elements preceeding the desired index, the element is added after the last non-null element.

        Parameters:
        index - The index to insert
        element - The element to add
